e function signatures clean and avoids changing any callers. The deployment will get the proxy environment variables applied automatically, and tests that don't set up the proxy informer will just skip that step.\n\nNow I'm mapping out the files that need changes: adding the proxy informer factory to the API discovery utilities, integrating it into the trust manager controller with the necessary getter method, applying the proxy environment in the deployments module, and setting up the manager initialization. I need to add the config client and informer imports to `setup_manager.go` since the generic utility function will need them to instantiate the proxy informer properly. I'm creating a generic function that discovers whether the Proxy API is available and initializes an informer if it is, then adding the necessary imports to the controller file.\n\nNow I'm modifying the Reconciler struct to include a proxy informer field that wraps the shared informer factory, and updating the New function signature to accept this informer as a parameter. Writing the proxy config method... Finishing the proxy environment variable setup... I need to add the missing imports for the config client, informers, and utils package to `setup_manager.go`, then modify the `NewControllerManager` function to initialize the config client when trust manager is enabled.\n\nContinuing with the setup, I'm creating a proxy informer using the config client's discovery mechanism and a shared informer factory, then checking if the proxy is applicable before adding it as a runnable to the manager so it can start and sync its cache. Finishing the error message for the reconciler creation, then checking the controller-runtime API to verify how `RunnableFunc` is defined and used...\n\nI see that `RunnableFunc` is a function type that implements the `Runnable` interface, so I can pass it directly to `mgr.Add()`. The `SharedInformerFactory.WaitForCacheSync` returns a map of type sync results rather than an