{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_vrtx_013PNYuXHFSyoM2Uz7rPVUwk","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I see that in the deployment tests, `testReconciler(t)` is used, which creates a Reconciler without a `proxyInformer`. Since my code guards with `r.proxyInformer == nil`, the `getClusterProxyConfig()` method will return nil, and `applyProxyEnv` will be a no-op. So existing tests will pass unchanged.\n\nNow let me finalize the complete implementation. Let me also check that `mgr.GetConfig()` is available.\n\nLet me think about one more thing: the `setup_manager.go` already imports `manager` from controller-runtime:\nChecking imports...\n\nFor the `RunnableFunc`, I need `context.Context`, which is already imported.\n\nAlright, I'm confident in my implementation. Let me produce the complete output.\n\nWait, one thing: I need to check if the `configv1.GroupVersion` constant can be used for the proxy GVR in apidiscovery.go, or if I should hardcode the group and version.\n\nSince `apidiscovery.go` is in the utils package and shouldn't depend on the OpenShift API, I'll hardcode the values to avoid adding a dependency on `configv1` in the utils package. But looking at the existing code, `starter.go` uses `configv1.GroupVersion.WithResource(\"infrastructures\")` to define the infra GVR, so I need to think about whether keeping the proxy GVR definition in apidiscovery.go with hardcoded values makes sense. The hardcoded values match what `configv1.GroupVersion` resolves to, so I'm confident they're correct. Now I'll write out the complete implementation for each file.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":6803,"cache_read_input_tokens":88178,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":6803,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":9},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"02c